Description: Seven small fragments of a dark brown and red-brown wool textile used as a wrapping. The weave is plain and is balanced in some places and warp/weft faced in others. The spinning direction of warp and weft is 's'. The thread count is warp 5 per 10mm and weft 9 per 10mm. The selvedge is plain with 3 cords.
Bibliographic references: Adams et al 1999 / Kulubnarti III: The Cemeteries (p. 62)
Acquisition name: Donated by: Dr William Yewdale Adams
Donated by: W S Webb Museum of Anthropology (University of Kentucky)
